Task 4: Sentiment Analysis
Goal: Automatically classify each review as Positive, Negative, or Neutral, and turn that into insights a business could actually use.
What's inside:

Used VADER (a lexicon-based NLP sentiment tool built for short, informal text like reviews)
Classified all 999 reviews and validated the results against actual star ratings (they line up well — sentiment score rises steadily from 1★ to 5★)
Built word clouds to see which words drive positive vs. negative sentiment
Tracked sentiment trend over time to spot shifts in customer opinion early
Identified specific products with lower average sentiment, even when their star rating looked fine
Summarized everything into business recommendations for marketing, product development, and customer support

Tools used: Python, VADER Sentiment, WordCloud, Pandas, Matplotlib, Seaborn
Key takeaway: Public sentiment is broadly positive, but the negative segment (roughly 1 in 5–6 reviews) contains clear, recurring themes — a goldmine for product and support teams to act on.
